         <abstract>
            <p>This year should witness the beginning of a substantial earnings recovery for the glass container industry. The price structure has improved greatly and the non-returnable soft drink bottle will produce material profits for the first time. Sales gains might exceed 7% annually and man-hour output will be helped by impressive technological changes. A commercial unbreakable bottle is expected within three to five years. In the can business, more moderate sales gains are anticipated as penetration of beer and soft drink markets slow down. Captive competition remains a major problem.</p>
